the meter. in almost all cases it is better to use the meter -- a negotiated fare means that you are being charged a higher than normal rate. a metered fare starts around ₹13, and includes the first kilometre of travel. never get in an auto-rickshaw without either the meter being turned on, or the fare negotiated in advance. in nearly all cases the driver will ask an exorbitant sum (for indian standards) from you later. a normal fare would be ₹11-12 for the first km and ₹7-8 per km after that. in most of the cities, auto-rickshaw drivers are 